.17-5.536C2.575 12.79.302 5.887 3.224 3.087c.868-.83 2.114-1.223 3.584-1.223 3.48 0 8.215 2.198 12.16 5.977 2.836 2.715 4.888 5.834 5.781 8.782.835 2.757.544 4.993-.818 6.298-.853.816-2.086 1.23-3.595 1.23-.902 0-1.903-.148-2.979-.448Z\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\" style=\"\"></path><path d=\"M16.813.521c-3.383.941-6.931 3.075-9.991 6.006C.25 12.823-1.931 20.596 1.855 24.223 3.111 25.426 4.843 26 6.838 26c4.016 0 9.096-2.33 13.486-6.536 6.57-6.295 8.752-14.068 4.967-17.695C24.067.597 22.366 0 20.34 0c-1.09 0-2.273.173-3.526.521ZM3.233 22.903c-1.358-1.3-1.645-3.53-.81-6.282.892-2.945 2.944-6.06 5.777-8.774 2.83-2.714 6.083-4.679 9.156-5.535 1.078-.299 2.079-.448 2.98-.448 1.503 0 2.73.412 3.578 1.225 1.356 1.3 1.644 3.531.81 6.282-.893 2.944-2.945 6.06-5.777 8.774-3.942 3.777-8.673 5.977-12.146 5.977-1.464 0-2.704-.39-3.568-1.219Z\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\" style=\"\"></path></g></svg></a></div></div></div></div><p>ROGERS, Ark. — Axle Payments, J.B. Hunt Transport and SkyBitz were voted as the top Day 1 demos by attendees at The Future of Supply Chain event on Monday.</p><p>The three companies were among the 17 demonstrations that presented live, seven-minute demos about products that will disrupt the freight industry. (<em><a href=\"https://www.freightwaves.com/news/hubtek-quickloadz-turvo-voted-top-demos-by-future-of-supply-chain-attendees\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Click here for Day 2 winners.</a></em>)</p><h2 id=\"h-axle-payments\">Axle Payments</h2><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0424-1200x675.jpg.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-427471\" srcset=\"https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0424-1200x675.jpg.webp 1200w, https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0424-600x338.jpg.webp 600w, https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0424-768x432.jpg.webp 768w, https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0424-1536x864.jpg.webp 1536w, https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0424-2048x1152.jpg.webp 2048w, https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0424-390x220.jpg.webp 390w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"><figcaption>Sean Smith and Shawn Vo demonstrate Axle Payment’s product. (Photo: Jim Allen/FreightWaves)</figcaption></figure><p>Axle Payments is a cash-flow management platform for freight brokers. Chief Technology Officer Shawn Vo and Head of Product Sean Smith demonstrated the company’s Axle Pro product.&nbsp;</p><p>Smith showed Axle Pro’s unique features that help brokers create efficiencies and save time with carriers and shippers. The goal is to create a FreightTech ecosystem that “uses strong relations to compound value for clients.”</p><p>“Our open API architecture allows us to be a hub that can integrate quickly to any TMS or accounting software, making Axle the only provider in the industry that serves as a one-stop, full-service platform,” the company said.</p><h2 id=\"h-j-b-hunt-transport\">J.B. Hunt Transport</h2><p>Mark Brewer, director of product innovation at J.B. Hunt Transport, demonstrated the Carrier 360 by J.B. Hunt product. Carrier 360 is a technology solution that addresses efficiency, cost savings and visibility across the supply chain.</p><div class=\"stream-item stream-item-in-post stream-item-inline-post aligncenter\"><div id=\"div-gpt-ad-1550535422102-0\" data-google-query-id=\"CJOm0bPO2fcCFVFnlgod848AoA\">  <div id=\"google_ads_iframe_/21776187881/fw-responsive-main_content-slot2_0__container__\" style=\"border: 0pt none; margin: auto; text-align: center;\"><iframe id=\"google_ads_iframe_/21776187881/fw-responsive-main_content-slot2_0\" name=\"google_ads_iframe_/21776187881/fw-responsive-main_content-slot2_0\" title=\"3rd party ad content\" width=\"468\" height=\"60\" scrolling=\"no\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" frameborder=\"0\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Advertisement\" tabindex=\"0\" srcdoc=\"\" data-google-container-id=\"2\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: bottom;\" data-load-complete=\"true\"></iframe></div></div></div><p>The product “provides access to an expansive multimodal marketplace for freight matching, and advanced tools and resources that streamline processes for efficiency,” the company said.&nbsp;</p><p>The demonstration showcased the technology that carriers can utilize “to access and operate multiple modes,” including intermodal dray, 360box power only and live loaded freight.</p><h2 id=\"h-skybitz\">SkyBitz</h2><figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0082-2-1200x675.jpg.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-427476\" srcset=\"https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0082-2-1200x675.jpg.webp 1200w, https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0082-2-600x338.jpg.webp 600w, https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0082-2-768x432.jpg.webp 768w, https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0082-2-1536x864.jpg.webp 1536w, https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0082-2-2048x1152.jpg.webp 2048w, https://s29755.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/DSC_0082-2-390x220.jpg.webp 390w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"><figcaption>SkyBitz on display at The Future Of Supply Chain. (Photo: Jim Allen/FreightWaves)</figcaption></figure><p>SkyBitz focuses on commercial telematics for transportation and logistics, oil and gas, and industrial markets. Senior Product Manager Debbie Sackman and Vice President Lisa Flynn demonstrated SkyBitz’s SkyCamera, SkyMobile and SkyMatch.</p><p>The SkyCamera system gives fleets a clear line of sight to trailer and cargo status. The smart camera scans the full length of the trailer to capture high-definition imagery and uses artificial intelligence to detect objects.</p><p>The SkyMobile app was also part of the presentation, along with SkyMatch, the company’s new tractor-trailer ID solution.</p><div class=\"stream-item stream-item-in-post stream-item-inline-post aligncenter\"><div id=\"div-gpt-ad-1550535506376-0\" data-google-query-id=\"CJSm0bPO2fcCFVFnlgod848AoA\">  <div id=\"google_ads_iframe_/21776187881/fw-responsive-main_content-slot3_0__container__\" style=\"border: 0pt none; margin: auto; text-align: center;\"><iframe id=\"google_ads_iframe_/21776187881/fw-responsive-main_content-slot3_0\" name=\"google_ads_iframe_/21776187881/fw-responsive-main_content-slot3_0\" title=\"3rd party ad content\" width=\"468\" height=\"60\" scrolling=\"no\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" frameborder=\"0\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Advertisement\" tabindex=\"0\" srcdoc=\"\" data-google-container-id=\"3\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: bottom;\" data-load-complete=\"true\"></iframe></div></div></div><p></p><p>The <a href=\"https://ratings.freightwaves.com/carriers/\">FREIGHTWAVES TOP 500</a> For-Hire Carriers list includes <a href=\"https://ratings.freightwaves.com/carriers/j-b-hunt/\">J.B. Hunt</a> (No. 4).</p><div class=\"post-bottom-meta post-bottom-tags post-tags-modern\"><div class=\"post-bottom-meta-title\"><span class=\"tie-icon-tags\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span> Tags</div><span class=\"tagcloud\"><a href=\"https://www.freightwaves.com/news/tag/2022-future-of-supply-chain\" rel=\"tag\">2022 Future Of Supply Chain</a> <a href=\"https://www.freightwaves.com/news/tag/axle-payments\" rel=\"tag\">Axle Payments</a> <a href=\"https://www.freightwaves.com/news/tag/jb-hunt-transport\" rel=\"tag\">J.B. Hunt Transport</a> <a href=\"https://www.freightwaves.com/news/tag/skybitz\" rel=\"tag\">SkyBitz</a></span></div>"}
